snippet.textDisplay: I am so glad they retained Nusrat Fateh Ali Khan Sahib’s iconic rendition of Allah Hoo at the end. No reimagining of this classic is complete without a nod to the maestro who first brought Bulleh Shah’s words to life. Beautifully performed, steeped in both a respectful nostalgia and an optimism for the future of Sufi music. Well done!
